  "note": "Each peptide stores both monoisotopic_mass and average_mass (Da). The pipeline picks which to compare based on the detected MS technique: high-res MS (ESI/Q-TOF) reports monoisotopic; most COAs labelled 'MW' quote average mass. 'verified' marks entries confirmed against an authoritative source (PubChem/literature). Seed values migrated from v0.1 are average_mass with verified=false \u2014 confirm before relying on MW-mismatch flags. Entries with is_blend=true are multi-component products with no single molecular weight; skip MW-mismatch checks for these. Entries with a variants[] array are species-ambiguous (e.g. peptide vs copper-complex, fragment vs full-length): the matcher should accept a COA mass that matches the primary OR any variant, and report which form matched rather than flagging a mismatch.",
